1.en: A war was about to begin on a certain planet. However, the rule of war decided by the no-tenki inhabitants of this planet was to compete for positions with anchor machines. Players will use anchor machines to unify 6 continents and 46 countries ... This game is a camp game where you skip anchors and increase your position. If you return the anchor that you flew with the anchor machine to your position within 3 shots, that will become your territory. However, you have to quickly expand your position while watching the wind direction, terrain, and the movement of the enemy. A game with high puzzle characteristics that requires the ability and strategy to make full use of various anchor machines.

2.en: A robot simulation game where you fight using the robot weapon "Armored Unit". You have to use radar to find and destroy invisible enemies. Two modes, "Story Mode" and "Duel Mode". In "Story Mode", the purpose is to prevent the completion of the enemy's final weapon by making full use of the mobile weapon armored unit. "Duel mode" is a mode to play against friends using a communication cable, and you can fight against friends using the units obtained or modified by the user in "Story mode".

3.en: A racing game where you modify and power up your own truck. In the WS version, there is a "national conquest mode" that aims to be the best tracker in Japan while fighting trackers all over the country while remodeling the truck, and a "communication confrontation mode" that fights by betting each other's truck parts using a communication cable powered by. In addition, the "Otoko no Hanamichi Mode" that was in the PS version has been integrated into the "National Conquest Mode" to further enhance the RPG-like elements! In addition to the parts that can be bought at the shop, the collection is also enhanced by preparing rare parts that can only be obtained from a specific tracker. Now, a new Dekotra legend begins with WS!

4.en: A game where you can easily enjoy the feeling of DJ. It's an interesting operation feeling, but it is made so that you can freely choose from three types of button arrangements according to the user's preference. However, if you don't feel like scratching with the shosen button, use the included special turntable controller. If you use an adapter with headphones (sold separately), you can hear even more powerful beats. For WS, 10 famous songs such as "SOUL", "FUNK", and "REGGAE" are collected in green.

5.en: Buffers Evolution is an Action game, developed and published by Bandai, which was released in Japan in 1999.

6.en: The popular character Chocobo is now available as software for handheld game consoles! That popular game "Chocobo's Mysterious Dungeon" is now available as WS-only software. Unpredictable game development, tense dungeons, item search, automatic dungeon generation function that changes every time you play, etc., do not spoil the fun of the original version. In addition, the powerful screen effects, huge enemy characters, and the best sound of handheld game consoles are all the features of WonderSwan. Now, in WonderSwan, it's an adventure with a cute chocobo!

7.en:
Jennifer Simpson is a child from the fictional Granite Orphanage in Romsdalen, Norway. She and her friends, who are also orphans (Laura, Ann and Lotte) are adopted in September 1995 (the same month the game was released) by a wealthy recluse named Mr. Barrows, who lives in a mansion known as the "Clock Tower", named after its predominant feature.

WS version of "Clock Tower" that scared many players with SFC / PS. Since it is compatible with stereo headphones, you can use headphones to reproduce realistic sound effects and sounds! You can enjoy the horror of running on your spine and the sound of a horror movie anytime, anywhere. The memory of fear revives again ...

8.en: Come one, come all! Watch the death-defying feats of a human fly - Crazy Climber! Help him scale the world's tallest buildings while avoiding tumbling girders, a marauding bird, and the villainous Mad Doctor. Hurry up! The show's about to start!

9.en: Densha de Go! is a Simulation game, developed and published by Taito Corporation, which was released in Japan in 1999.

10.en: Densha de Go! 2 is a Simulation game, developed by Taito Corporation and published by CyberFront, which was released in Japan in 1999.

11.en: The second in the Digimon series is an RPG that gathers friends while adventuring in the world of Digimon. By combining the collected Digimon, you can generate a special move called "Variable". Find the strongest Digimon and learn various "Variable Techniques" to create your own strongest Digimon unit! With a communication battle function that allows you to exchange Digimon with your friends and play against them.

12.en: Another version of "Digimon Adventure Anode Tamer" released in December 1999. There are a total of 169 types of Digimon that appear in this cathode tamer. Seven of them are original Digimon that appear only with cathode tamers. In addition to this, the appearance rate of Digimon is different from that of Anode Tamer, and the first enemy Digimon and boss characters are also different. There are changes in story development, and even users who already have an anode tamer can enjoy it. Since many Sea Digimon appear in the Cathode Tamer, you can enjoy it mainly by training attack-type units.

13.en: A mysterious story about why Ken-kun, also known as Digimon Kaiser, has entered the evil path. In addition to the conventional evolution, it also supports "Armor Evolution" and "Jogres Evolution", and new Digimon have joined, and more than 220 bodies have appeared. Players must play with both Ryo and Ken in a tag team to capture the digital world that exists in parallel. If you use a dedicated connector, you can battle with the conventional "Digimon series". If you use Wonder Wave, you can also use Digimon raised in D-One mode of PS software "Pocket Digimon World". In addition, jogress and digital exchange battle communication can be performed with "New Digivice D-3".

14.en: Digital Monster Ver. WonderSwan is a Japanese handheld version of the original Tamagotchi-like Digimon pet for the WonderSwan. It includes all of the original Digimon from the five different pet devices. In this game the player can have up to five different Digimon with them at a time. It even has computer controlled opponents to battle with. The game has the ability to connect to another WonderSwan through a special link cable. It can also hook up to the original pets through a Digimon "dock N rock" connector that comes packaged with the game. Digital Monster Ver. S: Digimon Tamers did much the same thing, only on the Sega Saturn.

15.en: Software that teaches words to Digimon while talking with them, and makes friends with them even more. Digimon fight using the words they remember, so the more words the player teaches, the stronger they become. The player can talk with two Digimon at the same time, and the Digimon can talk with each other, so the range of conversation is greatly expanded. There are 49 Digimon that appeared in the TV anime "Digimon Adventure" and 11 Digimon that are scheduled to appear in the new program "Digimon Adventure 02", for a total of 60 Digimon.

16.en: Dokodemo Hamster is a Strategy game, developed and published by Bec, which was released in Japan in 2000.

17.en: Game genre "stupid game". A puzzle game in which the character designed by "Uruma Rupi" of "Ugougo Luga" becomes drooling or covered with poop while aiming for clearing. It's a stupid, gloomy, and unpleasant game that makes players feel uncomfortable when they're done, creating an addiction that makes them want to see the screen being done. Besides, as a title song and voice actor, it is supervised by Brother Korn. Gross and cuteness are produced coolly (!?) By his hands.

18.en:
The Sankyo Fever series' sole WonderSwan entry.

Fever Sankyo Koushiki Pachinko Simulation for WonderSwan is a Miscellaneous game, developed and published by Bec, which was released in Japan in 1999.

19.en: Final Lap 2000 is a Racing game, developed by Soft Machine and published by Bandai, which was released in Japan in 2000.

20.en: The greatest pro wrestling simulator is now on Wonderswan, allowing you to bring the action with you anywhere you go. Involve yourself in MASTER OF RING, the new management mode taking you through the ranks of wrestling, and create a wrestling legend with the edit mode.

21.en: Ganso JaJaMaru-kun (元祖じゃじゃ丸くん?) is a remake of the video game Ninja JaJaMaru-kun released in Japan on April 15, 1999 by Jaleco for the WonderSwan. It is an enhanced version of the original Famicom game with better control, though it uses monochrome graphics due to being an original WonderSwan game

22.en: Glocal Hexcite is a Puzzle game, developed by Gu Inc and published by Success, which was released in Japan in 2000.

23.en: Goraku Ou Tango! is a Puzzle game, published by Mebius, which was released in Japan in 1999.

24.en: Gunpey is a Puzzle game, developed by Koto and published by Bandai, which was released in Japan in 1999.

25.en: Hanafuda Shiyouyo is a Miscellaneous game, published by Success, which was released in Japan in 2000.

26.en: A training game for "Haro" that appeared in Mobile Suit Gundam. On the planet Atius, the battle by Robopet's "Halo" is very popular. The player raises this Harobots and aims to become the strongest Harobots Butler. By playing 4 types of mini-games, Haro's ability will gradually increase. When the basic ability has risen to some extent, combine attributes and obtain new robot data. The obtained robot data can be used as Halo's transformation ability during battle. What's more, the robot data is the data of famous Sunrise robots such as Dunbine and Zambot 3, so I'm surprised! Of course, you can also exchange data and play against each other!

27.en: Bistro Recipe is a Strategy game, developed and published by Banpresto, which was released in Japan in 1999.

28.en: Klonoa and his friend Huepow come across a young crying girl who tells them that the moon has been divided into fragments and stolen by a mysterious group of artists that reside in the nearby Moonlight Museum. Determined to help, the duo rush off to the Museum's entrance, and once they come inside, they are greeted by a painter named Picoo who traps them inside a piece of artwork. Klonoa and Huepow must fight their way through five worlds within the Museum itself before finding the source of all their troubles and restoring the moon to the sky.

29.en: KISS Yori... Seaside Serenade is an Adventure game, developed and published by Kid, which was released in Japan in 1999.

30.en: Kosodate Quiz Dokodemo: My Angel is a Miscellaneous game, developed by Namco and published by Bandai, which was released in Japan in 1999.

31.en: Keiba is a Sports game, published by Bec, which was released in Japan in 1999.

32.en: Langrisser Millennium WS: The Last Century is a Strategy game, developed and published by Bandai, which was released in Japan in 2000.

33.en: Last Stand is a Strategy game, developed by Soft Machine and published by Bandai, which was released in Japan in 1999.

34.en: Lode Runner for WonderSwan is an Action game, developed by Aisystem Tokyo and published by Banpresto, which was released in Japan in 2000.

35.en: Macross: True Love Song is a Strategy game, developed and published by Lay-Up, which was released in Japan in 2000.

36.en: Magical Drop for WonderSwan is a Puzzle game, developed by Gaibrain and published by Data East, which was released in Japan in 1999.

37.en: Mahjong Touryuumon is a Miscellaneous game, developed by Chat Noir and published by Sammy Studios, which was released in Japan in 1999.

38.en:
Makaimura for WonderSwan (Japanese: 魔界村?, "Demon World Village for WonderSwan") is a game for the WonderSwan developed by Capcom and published by Bandai in 1999 and is part of the Ghosts 'n Goblins franchise.

Sharing similar gameplay to its predecessors, Makaimura also shares enemies, weapons and backgrounds from the previous three games. Unique features include double paths from the second till the fifth levels, swimming in water and a level which requires the player to rotate the wonderswan by 90 degrees as Arthur climbs and swings down a rope in a vertical shaft. Unlike other games, the player is not required to repeat the game after the penultimate level in order to get the one weapon to defeat the final boss Azrael.

39.en: An RPG set in the near future, where "robot battles (commonly known as robin)", in which robot pets and Medabots fight each other, are booming. Medabots consists of six parts: a tinpet corresponding to the skeleton, a medal corresponding to the brain, a head, a right arm, a left arm, and a leg, and there are 60 types of parts for each. By rearranging these parts, you can make your own Medabots. If you beat the enemy with Robottle, you can steal the opponent's parts, and you can also get the parts at the event. If you connect to your friend's Medabots with a communication cable, you can play against your friend's Medabots or exchange parts.

40.en: Meitantei Conan is an Adventure game, developed by Tomcat System and published by Bandai, which was released in Japan in 1999.

41.en: Meitantei Conan: Nishi no Meitantei Saidai no Kiki!? is an Adventure game, developed by Tomcat System and published by Bandai, which was released in Japan in 2000.

42.en:
Mingle Magnet is a simple puzzle game of the falling block variety. The player oversees a 10 x 10 square field where the first four rows (three on easy) have been filled by blocks. Each block shows one of three symbols, a dark gray circle, a light gray circle, and a white circle. When ever any of blocks with matching symbols touch they will form a link. By moving the cursor over a chain and clicking on it the player will be given points based on its size on the chain will be removed. The goal is to get a large score while making sure that new pieces can still enter the field. Once no more pieces can enter the game ends. Blocks fall at the same time one square apart, when the next set of blocks fall they will occupy the space given by the previous drop.

The "magnet" aspect of Mingle Magnet come into play in how the player can control the placement of the blocks. All the blocks are attracted to a magnet which, although not seen, can be placed on any side of the field. All blocks will be drawn to the magnet. For example, if one has the magnet at the south of the field and then puts it to the north what was the top of the block pile will now be the bottom, and blocks will fall onto what was the bottom. The direction of the magnet is indicated by a magnetic field animation behind the action.

This game is played vertically.

43.en: A simulation game. Players assume the role of an Anaheim Electronics test pilot as they utilize various Mobile Suits from Gundam's One Year War era.

44.en: Moero!! Pro Yakyuu Rookies is a Sports game, developed by TOSE and published by Jaleco Entertainment, which was released in Japan in 2000.

45.en: Neon Genesis Evangelion is a Role-Playing game, developed by Soft Machine and published by Bandai, which was released in Japan in 1999.

46.en: Nice On is a Sports game, developed by Aisystem Tokyo and published by Sammy Studios, which was released in Japan in 1999.

47.en: Tetsuman is a Miscellaneous game, developed by Chat Noir and published by Kaga Tech, which was released in Japan in 1999.

48.en: The popular series "Nobunaga's Ambition" has been renewed for WonderSwan! Enjoy the battle of the Sengoku daimyo who bet his life on the trade-in with new features such as heirloom exchange and war battle! !! Now is the time to become a turbulent Sengoku daimyo and aim to unify the world! Take command of the warlords under your control and get all 16 countries. In a breathtaking battle, you are the one who will fulfill your dream of unity. A new history is about to begin. Equipped with a new heirloom exchange system. Realize online battle play. There are more than 100 warlords. You can save 3 places.
